<div class="cc">

  <div class="cc-hero">
    <span class="cc-hero__label">Care Guide</span>
    <h1 class="cc-hero__title">Make it last.<br>Make it right.</h1>
    <p class="cc-hero__quote">Candles are simple objects.<br>But how you burn them changes everything.</p>
    <p class="cc-hero__sub">Follow these guidelines to get the best out of your candle — from the first light to the last.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="cc-grid">

    <div class="cc-card cc-card--y">
      <div class="cc-card__num">01</div>
      <div class="cc-card__title">First Burn</div>
      <div class="cc-card__sub">Let it melt properly.</div>
      <div class="cc-card__body">Allow the entire surface of the wax to melt to the edges on the first use. This prevents tunneling and ensures an even burn over time.<strong>→ Allow 2–3 hours minimum.</strong>
</div>
    </div>

    <div class="cc-card cc-card--r">
      <div class="cc-card__num">02</div>
      <div class="cc-card__title">Trim the Wick</div>
      <div class="cc-card__sub">Keep it clean.</div>
      <div class="cc-card__body">Before each burn, trim the wick to around 5 mm. This maintains a steady flame, reduces smoke, and extends the life of your candle.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="cc-card cc-card--b">
      <div class="cc-card__num">03</div>
      <div class="cc-card__title">Burn Time</div>
      <div class="cc-card__sub">Don't rush it.</div>
      <div class="cc-card__body">Burn your candle for a maximum of 3–4 hours at a time. Longer burns can overheat the wax and affect performance.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="cc-card cc-card--p">
      <div class="cc-card__num">04</div>
      <div class="cc-card__title">After Use</div>
      <div class="cc-card__sub">Let it rest.</div>
      <div class="cc-card__body">Extinguish with a snuffer — never blow or use water. Let the wax fully cool before moving the candle. Re-center the wick if needed.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="cc-card cc-card--y">
      <div class="cc-card__num">05</div>
      <div class="cc-card__title">When to Stop</div>
      <div class="cc-card__sub">Know when it's done.</div>
      <div class="cc-card__body">Stop using your candle when approximately 10 mm of wax remains. This prevents overheating of the container.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="cc-card cc-card--b">
      <div class="cc-card__num">06</div>
      <div class="cc-card__title">Keep it Clean</div>
      <div class="cc-card__sub">A better burn every time.</div>
      <div class="cc-card__body">Keep the wax surface free of dust and debris. A clean candle burns better and smells better — always.</div>
    </div>

  </div>

  <div class="cc-smart">
    <h2 class="cc-smart__title">Burn Smart</h2>
    <p class="cc-smart__sub">A few simple rules.</p>
    <ul class="cc-smart__rules">
      <li>Burn on a heat-resistant surface</li>
      <li>Keep away from drafts</li>
      <li>Keep away from flammable objects</li>
      <li>Never leave unattended</li>
      <li>Keep away from children &amp; pets</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="cc-finale">
    <span class="cc-finale__label">After the Flame</span>
    <h2 class="cc-finale__title">Objects first.<br>Candles second.</h2>
    <p class="cc-finale__body">Once finished, your vessel is made to stay. Reuse it. Keep it. Make it part of your space.</p>
    <a href="/collections/all" class="cc-finale__cta">Shop the Collection</a>
  </div>

</div>